{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which later was not the case, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the final result was that the-- and I experienced that my father was showing-- we were assembled again in the-- in the square and-- to do some work.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never knew what work they would do, where they will take us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the officer in charge spit on the passport, threw it down on the-- his documents, threw it down, stepped on them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he hit him twice in the face, and said, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was pretty hard for my father to take.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would consider my family to be religious, very religious, but with the kind of experience that my father had in World War I, I'm sure that he could not keep kosher where he was.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He probably was happy to get some food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he was-- he shaved, and he was more-- he was very religious, but not fanatically so.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My-- some of my uncles were extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wore the black [NON-ENGLISH], what they called, with the shtreimel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The shtreimel, which was-- did you ever hear the expressions, shtreimel was like a round-- it was sort of cut to-- to-- It was a good looking hat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was-- I remember my uncles wearing those, especially the Baders.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My grandfather, Wilhelm Enoch, was more of a showman, but he was also very religious, but not to the point how my grandfather Jacob Bader was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He always stayed in the corner and praying very hard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they both had beards, both of my grandfathers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the-- Jacob Bader was truly, I would not call it fanatically, but Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
